name: user-provider-application
description: The User Provider Application, developed with Java 17 and Spring Boot, is a critical microservice responsible for managing user data. This microservice handles all user-related activities, including profiles, settings, and follow-following functionalities. It is essential for maintaining comprehensive and user management within the system.

name: microservice
description: A Spring Boot microservices application showcasing distributed architecture with service registry, configuration management, API gateway, business services, data retrieval jobs, and observability using Zipkin.

name: ImageSharing-Microservice-Application-Typescript
description: A fully functional Image sharing microservice application, for saving and sharing beautiful pictures that matter to you. Built with Ionic, Node, Docker and Kubernetes.

name: web-analytics-microservice
description: Base Project for the Wikipedia/Twitter Analytics Micro Service  Application.

name: HospitalApplicationProject
description: This is Hospital Application Project  Using   In Spring Boot Monolithic vs Microservices And Spring Security Using Jwt Token And Creating Crud Operation

name: QuizApplication
description: This project is a comprehensive quiz application built using Spring Boot and microservices architecture. The application allows users to interact with a wide range of quizzes and questions, providing a robust platform for testing knowledge across various subjects.

name: MiniETicaret.MicroService
description: MiniETicaret.MicroService is a microservices-based e-commerce platform designed to demonstrate the scalability and flexibility of a modular architecture in a real-world application.

name: Microservices-Blog-Platform
description: Une application web moderne utilisant Node.js pour le backend et React pour le frontend,  déployée sur Kubernetes. Ce projet démontre une architecture microservices avec des composants distincts pour la gestion des posts,  des commentaires et la modération. Conteneurisé avec Docker et orchestré avec Kubernetes.

name: assignment-management-backend
description: Microservice web application to manage Assignment/Task Activities using Spring boot, MySQL, Eureka server.

name: modukafka
description: Spring Boot application with modular architecture, composed of two microservices that communicate with each other through Apache Kafka. One microservice sends messages and the other receives them.

name: UnitConversion
description: .NET library for the management of unit conversions deployed as NuGet's, a microservice, and a web application

name: kube_project
description: Ce projet est une application microservices construite avec Node.js et React. Il est conçu pour être déployé sur Kubernetes.

name: goffee-shop
description: goffee-shop is a food and beverage ordering application used in cafes and fast-food stores. Technically, the system consists of microservices written in Golang.

name: personalized-recommendation-engine
description: This is a microservice-based application designed to track user behavior and provide personalized recommendations based on that behavior. The application leverages a combination of Golang, Flask, and Kafka to deliver a scalable and efficient recommendation system.

name: trafic-toll-calculator
description: A microservices-based system designed to calculate traffic tolls for trucks, with potential applications in broader logistics operations. The system leverages modern technologies to ensure scalability, efficiency, and real-time processing.

name: FastAPI
description: Dependency Injection (DI), Object Relational Mappers (ORMs), Building the Microservice Application, Object Document Mapper (ODMs), Security - JWT, Keycloak, Okta, and Auth0, asynchronous background processes using Celery, asynchronous messaging using RabbitMQ and Apache Kafka, SSE, WebSocket, and asynchronous events.

name: tutoring-website
description: An unreleased web application built by team of six for soliciting/offering tutoring in academic or recreational disciplines within an organization. The app is built on the MERN tech stack with additional integrated microservices to offer LinkedIn-style analytics and messaging capabilities.
